cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CAST: Coordinated Agent Swarm Testing"
message: "If you use CAST in research, please cite the original paper."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Golston
    given-names: Julie
    affiliation: Scaffold Studios
    email: hello@scaffoldstudios.com
repository-code: "https://gitlab.com/scaffoldstudios/cast"
url: "https://scaffoldstudios.com/cast"
abstract: >-
  CAST (Coordinated Agent Swarm Testing) is a methodology and open-source
  framework that deploys 100 LLM-powered agents organized into five specialized
  squads to perform structured static analysis of web application source code
  as a cost-effective substitute for human beta testing.
keywords:
  - software testing
  - multi-agent systems
  - large language models
  - beta testing
  - static analysis
  - LLM agents
  - AI-assisted development
license: Apache-2.0
